The evidence with the title 'Healthcare in Canada - Wikipedia ' says In the USA, 13.6 per cent of GNP is used on medical care. By contrast, in Canada, only 9.5 per cent of GNP is used on the medicare system, “ in part because there is no profit incentive for private insurers. ”Lightman also notes that the in-kind delivery system eliminates much of the advertising that is prominent in the USA,  ... 
